 :Don't do that then!: imp. [from an old doctor's office joke about a patient
with a trivial complaint] Stock response to a user complaint. "When I type
control-S, the whole system comes to a halt for thirty seconds." "Don't do
that, then!" (or "So don't do that!"). Compare {RTFM}. Here's a classic
example of "Don't do that then!" from Neal Stephenson's "In The Beginning Was
The Command Line". A friend of his built a network with a load of Macs and a
few high-powered database servers. He found that from time to time the whole
network would lock up for no apparent reason. The problem was eventually
tracked down to MacOS's cooperative multitasking: when a user held down the
mouse button for too long, the network stack wouldn't get a chance to run...